          "prompt_html": "<h1>MULTIPLE CHOICE 54</h1><p><strong>Questions 31 - 36</strong></p><p>For each question, choose <strong>TWO</strong> correct options.</p><p>Write the letters <strong>A - E</strong>, in any order in answer boxes.</p><p>Which <strong>TWO</strong> facts are true?</p><p>High-rise developments in cities...</p><p>31</p><p>32</p><table><thead><tr><th><strong>A</strong></th><th>...lead to the phenomenon of ‘urban sprawl’.</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td><strong>B</strong></td><td>...create pockets of open land surrounded by buildings.</td></tr><tr><td><strong>C</strong></td><td>...can cause feelings of disconnection from the natural world.</td></tr><tr><td><strong>D</strong></td><td>...require a lot of resources and infrastructure.</td></tr><tr><td><strong>E</strong></td><td>...increase air pollution in cities.</td></tr></tbody></table><p>Which <strong>TWO</strong> facts are true?</p><p>The Vertical Forest project...</p><p>33</p><p>34</p><table><thead><tr><th><strong>A</strong></th><th>...consists of two high-rise blocks.</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td><strong>B</strong></td><td>...provides hotel accommodation and office space.</td></tr><tr><td><strong>C</strong></td><td>...overlooks the Cathedral of Milan.</td></tr><tr><td><strong>D</strong></td><td>...includes 900 trees planted on balconies.</td></tr><tr><td><strong>E</strong></td><td>...covers 7,000 square metres of land.</td></tr></tbody></table><p>Which <strong>TWO</strong> facts are true?</p><p>The vegetation at the Vertical Forest...</p><p>35</p><p>36</p><table><thead><tr><th><strong>A</strong></th><th>...is aesthetically pleasing.</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td><strong>B</strong></td><td>...helps to improve the air quality in the city.</td></tr><tr><td><strong>C</strong></td><td>...is protected by special dust filters.</td></tr><tr><td><strong>D</strong></td><td>...allows people to use balconies without being seen.</td></tr><tr><td><strong>E</strong></td><td>...increases the humidity inside the buildings.</td></tr></tbody></table>",
